RACE.RACE_TEXT: Century Downs Aged Invitational S. CENTURY DOWNS RACE 1 400 Y Dirt CR: 81. Invitational Stakes Purse 21640. A STAKES RACE FOR THREE YEAR OLD & UPWARD QUARTER HORSES. Time of Entry $200. Preferences as per the AQHRA. Weight 124 lbs 3 Year Old, 126 lbs Older.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLIGHT CLUB rallied midstretch, and pulled off late under confident handling. JESSAPRIMADONNA responded to urging when leaving the chute but was no match for the winner. FIRELICIOUS broke outward, and surged late to score the show. TIMBERS EXPRESS broke awkwardly, and was outkicked. BEARCAT BILL late mild rally. SHE WEARS THE PANTZ weakened late. SCARLETTS CARTEL lacked a kick needed.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Alberta Bred Derby CENTURY DOWNS RACE 2 400 Y Dirt CR: 73. Derby Purse 36696. A DERBY FINAL FOR ACCREDITED ALBERTA BRED THREE-YEAR-OLD QUARTER HORSES WHO QUALIFIED FOR THE ALBERTA BRED DERBY FINAL. Weight 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NORTHFORK BOSS brushed leaving, gained outside midstretch, dug in late, and inched clear. HEZA MAJESTIC HERO rallied midstretch and was outfinished. JUNK DRAWER jostled away then sped to the front and was caught in the final yards. TULSA TIMBER bumped leaving, rallied then flattened out. SPRINGELEER broke outward into NORTHFORK BOSS, and closed late. FDD FAST MAN some early speed and weakened. EYEMADASHIN bumped leaving, flashed early speed and gave way. APPRECIATE stumbled then was bumped away from the gate, and was unable to recover from the start.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Birdcatcher S. CENTURY DOWNS RACE 4 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 68. Stakes Purse 50000. A STAKE FOR TWO-YEAR-OLDS. A fee of $100.00 required to nominate. A payment of $500.00 is required to pass the entry box and an additional $400.00 is required to start. The purse will be divided $30,000 to the owner of the winner, $10,000 to the second pl ace finisher, $5,000 to the third place finisher, $2,500 to the fourth place finisher and $1,000 to the fifth place finisher. A payment of $500 will be paid to all horses who start and finish 6th or worse. Starters to be named through the entry box by the closing time of entries. The field will be limited to 10 starters. Preference will be given to those horses with the highest lifetime earnings at time of entry. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Colts and Geldings : 124 lbs. Fillies : 12 1 lbs. Maidens allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRATED COCONUT sat just off the pace from the two path, drew away when asked and was ridden out. SUDDENLY FAMOUS set the pace, was unable to move on with rival, and finished evenly. SAWCHUK stalked the pacesetters early and lacked a kick that was needed.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Freedom of the City S. CENTURY DOWNS RACE 5 7 1/2F Dirt CR: 63. Stakes Purse 50000. A STAKE FOR TWO-YEAR-OLD FILLIES. A fee of $100.00 required to nominate. A payment of $500.00 is required to pass the entry box and an additional $400.00 is required to start. The purse will be divided $30,000 to the owner of the winner, $10,000 to the se cond place finisher, $5,000 to the third place finisher, $2,500 to the fourth place finisher and $1,000 to the fifth place finisher. A payment of $500.00 will be paid to all horses who start and finish 6th or worse. Starters to be named through the entry box by the closing time of entries. The field will be limited to 10 starters. Preference will be given to those horses with the highest earnings. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Fillies : 123 lbs. Maidens allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SILKSTONE vied three wide in the opening stages, emerged the leader into the backstretch, repelled a bid at the head of the stretch, and kicked clear under mild handling. MORNING RAIN vied between foes entering the first turn, cut the corner into the backstretch, shifted out to the two path tracking the leader, and was no match for the winner late. BROKEN PROMISES trailed the field early, went in pursuit of the leaders but was unable to get near. KULSUM vied inside, checked when leaving the opening turn, and yielded. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Board of Stewards conducted an inquiry in the opening turn and after review determined that MORNING RAIN caused interference to KULSUM. MORNING RAIN was disqualified from second and placed fourth for interference.

ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, cut corner, shifted out 2pth, no match

TEE CLASS tracked inside early, chased through the far turn, but was no match for leaders in the stretch. BORN ON FIRE vied inside, dropped back then drifted out entering the backstretch, and tired. MY BOY CHRISTIAN vied inside between foes to the opening turn, drew away, was overtaken leaving the backstretch, and wilted.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GWIZZ showed early speed then stalked the early pace, moved up alongside MILITARY SASS to challenge the front, dueled through the stretch, dug in the final yards, and inched clear. MILITARY SASS set a pressured pace, dueled inside of GWIZZ through the stretch, and was narrowly out-finished. DARKCLOUDOFSMOKE trailed the field throughout and closed late to earn show honors. HERE'S LEXIE reserved off the early pacesetters, was no match for the leaders through the stretch and was edged out late for third. SHES A COOL CAT showed a mild interest late. BONNIE AND MOE lacked early speed and was outrun. GOTTALOVETHATGIRL outrun throughout.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE ITALIAN MAN tracked from the second flight while four wide, exchanged bumps with LAHUN in the backstretch, rallied five to six wide at the head of the lane, match strides with LAHUN through the drive, and narrowly prevailed. LAHUN returned to the paddock for a tack adjustment, reserved off the early pacesetters, exchanged bumps inside of THE ITALIAN MAN, drove three to four wide in the final turn, dueled in the stretch and was out-finished. AMEER trailed the field early, bid inside then lacked running room into the stretch, and improved late to score show. DADDY'S PEPPER prompted the early pace outside of FAVORITE LIGHT, flattened in stretch then was caught. BOBS BUDDY went three to four wide into the opening turn, gained closer order in the final turn, and passed tiring rival. FAVORITE LIGHT returned to the paddock for a tack adjustment, set a pressured pace, was overtaken nearing the final turn and wilted abruptly. CAROSWAY showed little.
